An NYPD cruiser slammed into a pedestrian in Brooklyn while responding to a robbery Tuesday afternoon, authorities said. The victim, a 60-year-old man, was crossing 86th Street in Bath Beach at about 3:20 p.m. when he was struck by the marked police SUV, cops said. The police vehicle had its sirens and lights activated at the time of the collision, officials said. The pedestrian was taken to Lutheran Hospital in stable condition, according to the NYPD. Detectives were examining a plastic bag and a pillow left in the street in front of the vehicle, photos showed.